              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of χάσμα ‘yawning,’ not occurring in the NT) a deep, unbridgeable valley or trough between two points</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>chasm</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In this only NT occurrence of χάσμα the reference is to the impassable space between two parts of the supernatural abode of the dead. Translators frequently use a descriptive phrase such as ‘a deep valley which no one may cross’ or ‘a space which cannot be crossed.’</Comments>
